  "title": "You've Been Served",
  "description": "In this comedic one-woman show, Noemi Zeigler gets served divorce papers on the top of a garbage bin, reigniting her dream to be a singer. A record producer slash spiritual guru leads her on an ayahuasca-fuelled trip",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Noemi Zeigler<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Dramaturgy by David Ford<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Noemi Zeigler<br/>",
  "website": "https://madelineminx.com SOCIALS @madelineminx",
  "plain_language": "In this funny one-woman show, Noemi Zeigler gets divorce papers while taking out the garbage. This moment makes her want to become a singer again. A music producer who is also a spiritual guru offers her a record deal and gives her a plant medicine that takes her on a wild trip. She joins a cult, gets baptized in a swimming pool, and learns that perimenopause is kind of like going through puberty all over again.",
